Monique Marks, head of Urban Future Centre at DUT
Video: Karen Singh
 

Malusi Mbatha, former user and current chairperson of SANPUD explained that the Step up mobile unit that facilitates NSP program goes out into the streets to look for the syringes and needles.
"Whenever we do cleanups, we take each and every needle. We take other people's needles, not just our own because if there are needles lying around and there is a disease in that needle others will contract that disease." said Mbatha.

A memorandum and signed petition was delivered to the mayor's office asking for the reinstatement of the project.
The Mercury